Weise Says Germany Needs Two Million Migrants, Die Welt Reports

-- B y   J e f f   B l a c k
-- 
2011-05-14T10:00:59Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-14/weise-says-germany-needs-two-million-migrants-die-welt-reports.html
German Labor Agency Chief Frank- Juergen Weise said the country needs more than two million
qualified immigrants to alleviate the shortage of skilled
workers,  Die Welt  reported.  Weise told the newspaper that by 2025  Germany  would need as
many as seven million additional skilled workers, not all of
whom could come from the domestic labor pool.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jeff Black in Frankfurt 
